allowance(address,address,uint256).details: Returns the amount of token `id` that `spender` can spend on behalf of `owner`.

approve(address,uint256,uint256).details: Sets `amount` as the allowance of `spender` for the caller for token `id`. Emits a {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address,uint256).details: Returns the amount of token `id` owned by `owner`.

burn(address,uint256[],uint256[]).details: this seems dangerous. be careful to not lock up any underlying assets!

decimals(uint256).details: Returns the number of decimals for token `id`. Returns 18 by default. Please override this function if you need to return a custom value.

isOperator(address,address).details: Checks if a `spender` is approved by `owner` to manage all of their tokens.

setOperator(address,bool).details: Sets whether `operator` is approved to manage the tokens of the caller. Emits {OperatorSet} event.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Returns the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for token `id`.

transfer(address,uint256,uint256).details: Transfers `amount` of token `id` from the caller to `to`. Requirements: - caller must at least have `amount`. Emits a {Transfer} event.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256,uin.details: Transfers `amount` of token `id` from `from` to `to`. Note: Does not update the allowance if it is the maximum uint256 value. Requirements: - `from` must at least have `amount` of token `id`. -  The caller must have at least `amount` of allowance to transfer the    tokens of `from` or approved as an operator. Emits a {Transfer} event.

allowedBurners(address).notice: keep track of old game logic so that they can keep the ability to burn. otherwise tokens could be stuck!
